{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/organisations/council-for-science-and-technology/about","content_id":"5f5a4c93-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef","description":"The Council for Science and Technology (CST) provides independent advice to the Prime Minister on science and technology policy issues across government.","details":{"attachments":[],"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><h2 id=\"who-we-are\">Who we are</h2>\n\n<p>The Council for Science and Technology (<abbr title=\"Council for Science and Technology\">CST</abbr>) was established in 1993 as the government’s top-level advisory body on science and technology. <abbr title=\"Council for Science and Technology\">CST</abbr> is co-chaired by the Government Chief Scientific Adviser and an independent chair. The Council is formed of 19 independent <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/council-for-science-and-technology/about/membership\">members</a>.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"governance\">Governance</h2>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/council-for-science-and-technology/about/terms-of-reference\">Terms of reference</a>.</li>\n  <li>\n<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/cst-ways-of-working\">Ways of working</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"responsibilities\">Responsibilities</h2>\n\n<p>The Council provides impartial and evidence-based advice to the Prime Minister and Cabinet on:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>what the government’s high-level priorities for science and technology should be to deliver the government’s national missions;</li>\n  <li>emerging and long-term scientific and technological developments, including opportunities and risks relating to:\n    <ul>\n      <li>science and research capability</li>\n      <li>innovation and economic growth</li>\n      <li>health and quality of life within the UK</li>\n      <li>sustainable development and resilience</li>\n    </ul>\n  </li>\n  <li>how science, technology, engineering and mathematics (<abbr title=\"science, technology, engineering and mathematics\">STEM</abbr>) can be developed and sustained in the UK (e.g., through skills and international partnerships);</li>\n  <li>the UK’s science and innovation system, including issues relating to UK research, development, and innovation institutions;</li>\n  <li>other matters requested by the Prime Minister, ministers, or considered important by the Council; and</li>\n  <li>topics requested by the Science and Technology Cabinet Committee.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"code-of-practice\">Code of practice</h2>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"Council for Science and Technology\">CST</abbr> adopts the government’s <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/scientific-advisory-committees-code-of-practice\">Code of Practice for Scientific Advisory Committees</a> although, as the <abbr title=\"Council for Science and Technology\">CST</abbr>’s role is to advise on strategic policy rather than to evaluate research, some parts of the code aren’t directly relevant to <abbr title=\"Council for Science and Technology\">CST</abbr>’s activities.</p>\n\n<p>The code covers all of the committee’s work including role, remit, responsibilities of members, chairs and secretariats, working practices, and publication of documents. It ensures that the committee works openly and transparently.</p>\n\n</div>","change_history":[{"note":"The summary of the Council for Science and Technology has been updated.","public_timestamp":"2025-08-08T11:56:38Z"},{"note":"Updating a spelling error. ","public_timestamp":"2025-04-07T15:35:52Z"},{"note":"Updated to edit the summary. Updated to edit 'Who we are' and 'Responsibilities'. \r\nUpdated to add 'Code of practice' and 'Governance', including links to terms of reference and ways of working. Updated to remove 'History of CST', 'Priorities', and 'Jobs and contracts'.\r\n","public_timestamp":"2025-02-03T09:00:00Z"},{"note":"Changed the description of the Council for Science and Technology to signpost to the government body which provides the Council’s secretariat.","public_timestamp":"2023-10-25T14:26:17Z"},{"note":"Added in a section on the history of CST","public_timestamp":"2023-09-22T10:34:41Z"},{"note":"Updated priorities for 2023.","public_timestamp":"2023-03-08T08:28:30Z"},{"note":"Updated priorities for 2022.","public_timestamp":"2022-03-23T12:16:48Z"},{"note":"Priorities updated.","public_timestamp":"2020-10-06T16:13:09Z"},{"note":"Updated priorities.","public_timestamp":"2017-08-29T16:12:37Z"},{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2014-01-06T13:58:32Z"}],"corporate_information_groups":[{"contents":["5f55ef06-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef","5f55db44-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef","5f55ef5c-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef"],"name":"Access our information"},{"contents":[{"title":"Jobs","url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/council-for-science-and-technology/about#jobs-and-contracts"}],"name":"Jobs and contracts"}],"headers":[{"id":"who-we-are","level":2,"text":"Who we are"},{"id":"governance","level":2,"text":"Governance"},{"id":"responsibilities","level":2,"text":"Responsibilities"},{"id":"code-of-practice","level":2,"text":"Code of practice"}],"organisation":"fbc49af1-eb3a-4d17-9503-a3c249b8eee4","tags":{"browse_pages":[]}},"document_type":"about","first_published_at":"2014-01-06T13:58:32+00:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/council-for-science-and-technology/about","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/council-for-science-and-technology/about","base_path":"/government/organisations/council-for-science-and-technology/about","content_id":"5f5a4c93-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef","document_type":"about","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-08-08T11:56:38Z","schema_name":"corporate_information_page","title":"About us","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/council-for-science-and-technology/about","withdrawn":false}],"corporate_information_page